From: qian.wang <qian.wang@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH] [Bugfix][Gemma4] Align ModelOpt MIXED_PRECISION quantized_layers
 keys with runtime FusedMoE prefix

When loading a Gemma4 checkpoint quantized via ModelOpt with mixed precision
(e.g. NVFP4 experts + FP8 attention/dense MLP), the FusedMoE layers fall back
to ``UnquantizedFusedMoEMethod`` because their quant entries cannot be found.

Root cause 1 — prefix mismatch:

ModelOpt checkpoints emit ``model.<...>.layers.N.experts`` to match the HF
Transformers ``Gemma4DecoderLayer`` layout, while vLLM's ``Gemma4MoE`` wraps
the experts and registers ``FusedMoE`` under ``...layers.N.moe.experts``.
Per-tensor expert weight names are already remapped in ``_weight_iterator``
via ``_remap_gemma4_expert_weight_name``, so weights load correctly. However,
the ``hf_to_vllm_mapper`` previously had no rule for the parent-module entry,
so ``ModelOptMixedPrecisionConfig.apply_vllm_mapper -> apply_dict`` never
rewrote the ``quantized_layers`` keys. ``get_quant_method`` then queried
``...layers.N.moe.experts`` and missed the ``...layers.N.experts`` entry,
falling back to unquantized.

Root cause 2 — double mapping:

``apply_vllm_mapper`` is called twice on the same quant config object: once
from ``VllmConfig.__post_init__`` (via ``_get_quantization_config``) and once
from ``initialize_model`` -> ``configure_quant_config``. Without a guard, the
``.experts`` -> ``.moe.experts`` regex fires twice, producing
``.moe.moe.experts`` — which again fails lookup.

Fix:

1. Add a regex rule to both ``Gemma4ForCausalLM`` and
   ``Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration`` weight mappers that rewrites the parent
   ``.experts`` suffix.

2. Make ``ModelOptMixedPrecisionConfig.apply_vllm_mapper`` idempotent with a
   ``_vllm_mapper_applied`` guard flag.

Effect:
* Affects only the two Gemma4 wrapper classes — other models keep their
  own mappers.
* For non-mixed Gemma4 quantization paths (full NVFP4, full FP8, or BF16),
  ``ModelOptMixedPrecisionConfig`` is not used, so both fixes are inert.
* The idempotent guard is a general safety improvement — it prevents
  double-mapping regardless of which model class triggers it.

After this fix, vLLM logs ``Using 'VLLM_CUTLASS' NvFp4 MoE backend`` instead
of ``Using TRITON Unquantized MoE backend`` for Gemma4 mixed-precision
checkpoints.

---
diff --git a/vllm/model_executor/layers/quantization/modelopt.py b/vllm/model_executor/layers/quantization/modelopt.py
index 092346cb3..289401d8f 100644
--- a/vllm/model_executor/layers/quantization/modelopt.py
+++ b/vllm/model_executor/layers/quantization/modelopt.py
@@ -2372,6 +2372,14 @@ class ModelOptMixedPrecisionConfig(ModelOptQuantConfigBase):
         return None
 
     def apply_vllm_mapper(self, hf_to_vllm_mapper: "WeightsMapper"):
+        # Idempotent: apply_vllm_mapper is called twice on the same quant config
+        # object (once from VllmConfig.__post_init__ via _get_quantization_config,
+        # and once from initialize_model -> configure_quant_config). Without this
+        # guard the `.experts` -> `.moe.experts` regex would fire twice, producing
+        # `.moe.moe.experts` and failing the lookup again.
+        if getattr(self, "_vllm_mapper_applied", False):
+            return
+        self._vllm_mapper_applied = True
         super().apply_vllm_mapper(hf_to_vllm_mapper)
         if self.quantized_layers:
             self.quantized_layers = hf_to_vllm_mapper.apply_dict(self.quantized_layers)
diff --git a/vllm/model_executor/models/gemma4.py b/vllm/model_executor/models/gemma4.py
index 75f6945cc..4dd057f8f 100644
--- a/vllm/model_executor/models/gemma4.py
+++ b/vllm/model_executor/models/gemma4.py
@@ -1507,6 +1507,15 @@ class Gemma4ForCausalLM(
     nn.Module, SupportsLoRA, SupportsPP, MixtureOfExperts, SupportsEagle3
 ):
     hf_to_vllm_mapper = WeightsMapper(
+        orig_to_new_regex={
+            # Rewrite the parent-module entry `.experts` -> `.moe.experts` so that
+            # ModelOptMixedPrecisionConfig.get_quant_method finds the FusedMoE
+            # quant entry via its vLLM-side prefix. Per-tensor expert weight names
+            # are already handled by `_remap_gemma4_expert_weight_name` inside
+            # `_weight_iterator`; this mapper is for the parent-module key in
+            # `quantized_layers` (rewritten via `apply_vllm_mapper`).
+            re.compile(r"\.experts$"): ".moe.experts",
+        },
         orig_to_new_prefix={
             # Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration already loads the text stack
             # from `model.language_model.*`. We reuse that same checkpoint
diff --git a/vllm/model_executor/models/gemma4_mm.py b/vllm/model_executor/models/gemma4_mm.py
index 91be7d47f..8f2c0d604 100644
--- a/vllm/model_executor/models/gemma4_mm.py
+++ b/vllm/model_executor/models/gemma4_mm.py
@@ -934,6 +934,12 @@ class Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration(
 
     # Maps checkpoint prefixes to vLLM module paths.
     hf_to_vllm_mapper = WeightsMapper(
+        orig_to_new_regex={
+            # Rewrite the parent-module entry `.experts` -> `.moe.experts` so that
+            # ModelOptMixedPrecisionConfig.get_quant_method finds the FusedMoE
+            # quant entry via its vLLM-side prefix.
+            re.compile(r"\.experts$"): ".moe.experts",
+        },
         orig_to_new_prefix={
             "model.embed_audio.": "embed_audio.",
             "model.embed_vision.": "embed_vision.",
@@ -942,7 +948,7 @@ class Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration(
             "model.audio_tower.": "audio_tower.",
             "lm_head.": "language_model.lm_head.",
             "model": "language_model.model",
-        }
+        },
     )
 
     def __init__(self, *, vllm_config: VllmConfig, prefix: str = ""):
